dhesi@rahul.net (Rahul Dhesi) writes:

[...]
>The key escrow scheme assumes that a
>government agency that has half of the key can do nothing useful with
>it alone.  How true is this assumption?
[...]

My understanding is that each escrow agency gets an 80-bit sequence.
To create the real 80-bit key, these sequences are XORed together.

If this is implemented well, nothing useful can be done
with "half" a key.

- Carl

